    <h3>District Information</h3>
    <p>Serving over 35,000 students, the Shawnee Mission School District takes educating its students seriously.  Making "America's Best Schools" list in Newsweek, and ranked as in the top 4% school nationwide is just one way this district proves itself.  Creating a safe, yet efficient, learning environment is a standard this district believes in.  Providing students with effective tools to develop moral reasoning, a sense of pride and higher levels of thinking is a top priority.  Giving them many AP courses, specialty classes, and clubs to join allows students to discover their own passions and abilities.  A variety of different sports are open each season, and teams have won competitions, including state championships and regional titles.  Students in this district also compete in scholarly competitions, such as the National Merit Scholarship Program.  Proven to be a successful foundation for students' future, Shawnee Mission School District continues to provide excellent education.</p>
